result.execSummary:
The defendant Garit M Pedersen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Garit M Pedersen is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Garit M Pedersen was found guilty of Manuf/Deliver Amphetamine(>50g) [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)4.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Meet with DOC representative within 48 business hours.

miscConds.notes: Court costs and DNA surcharge totaling of $518.00. Cash bond applied, paid in full.  Refund balance.

The Defendant, being found guilty of a felony or other crime specified in sub.(1) under Wisconsin Stats. Sec. 941.29 under the Wisconsin Criminal Code of requirements and penalties,  is prohibited from possessing, receiving, or obtaining a firearm/body armor."

Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety and no consumption of illegal drugs.  Defendant not to possess any alcohol or illegal substances or drug paraphernalia.  Defendant not to enter any establishments where alcohol primarily served/sold except for employment purposes..   Defendant to take medications as prescribed by treating physician.

Note:  Under Wisconsin State Statute 6.03(1)(b), as a person found guilty of a felony that you are ineligible to vote in any election until your civil rights are restored.

Defendant is to enter, participate in, and successfully complete any assignments,evaluations, and/or treatment programs as directed by the Agent, and may not withdraw from any treatment programs involved in unless given permission from Agent and the treatment provider.
Defendant is to submit DNA sample.
Cooperate with and complete AODA Assessment and follow through on all recommendations of Counselor.

timeConds.notes: Huber release granted, hours and conditions to be set by Sheriff's Dept. Day-for-day credit for successfull completion of Criminal Justice Programming.
